The client receives the website's content when the host connects to it: The host requests the web page or resource using the transport-layer protocol (such as TCP or UDP) and port number. The website retrieves the requested web page or resource from its server. The website transmits the host the requested web page or resource and any related data or media. The host analyzes the web page response and displays it on the client device. In summary, the host sends a request to the website using the transport-layer protocol and the proper port number, the website responds with the desired web page or resource, and the host receives, processes, and displays it on the client device. 